{
  "texts": [
    "One-hot encoding is a simple vectorization approach in text processing.",
    "In this approach, an essay with N words is represented as sparse binary vectors.",
    "Each word in the essay is represented by a binary vector of length N, where only the index corresponding to the word is assigned a value of 1, while the rest of the elements in the vector are set to 0.",
    "One-hot representation were utilized in Taghipour and Ng (2016) to construct a lookup table layer.",
    "This representation is sparse, with all entries being zero except for the word that the vector represents."
  ]
}